Prism v0.1 (2023-03-27)
------------------------
* Added
  - PySCF interface
  - pc-NEVPT2 amplitudes
  - CVS-IP-MR-ADC(2) energies

Prism v0.2 (2023-05-12)
------------------------
* Added
  - CVS-IP-MR-ADC(2)-X energies
  - CVS-IP-MR-ADC(2) intensities
  - CVS-IP-MR-ADC(2)-X intensities

Prism v0.2.1 (2023-07-04)
------------------------
* Added
  - Efficient combinations of einsum terms containing 3-RDMs and 4-RDMs

Prism v0.3 (2023-09-15)
------------------------
* Added
  - Support to density-fitting 2e- integrals
  - Spectroscopic factors analysis for CVS-IP-MR-ADC

Prism v0.3.1 (2023-12-12)
------------------------
* Added
  - Effective Hamiltonian integrals consistent with CASSCF/CASCI reference
  - Support to store expensive amplitudes (t1_ccee and t1_caee) on disk
  - Efficient calculation of contractions containing v_ooee and t_ooee tensors

Prism v0.4 (2024-01-22)
------------------------
* Added
  - Memory efficient procedures to read H5PY files

Prism v0.8 (2025-03-26)
------------------------
* Added
  - Fully internally contracted NEVPT2 energies with frozen core and density fitting support
  - Support of state-averaged CASSCF reference wavefunctions for the state-specific NEVPT2 calculations
  - Improved interface to the NEVPT2 and MR-ADC modules
  - Improved output and summary of results
  – Better handling of short tests
  - New tests for CVS-IP-MR-ADC and NEVPT2
* Fixes
  - Fixed bugs in CVS-IP-MR-ADC transition moments when using small max_memory
  - Fixed bugs in open-shell CVS-IP-MR-ADC calculations introduced during the interface update

Prism v0.9 (2026-03-18)
------------------------
* Added:
   - General state-interaction spin–orbit coupling code (SOC) within spin–orbit mean-field approximation with Breit–Pauli and exact two-component Douglas–Kroll–Hess Hamiltonians (currently restricted to half-integer spin systems)
   - Calculations of magnetic g-tensors using the SOC-perturbed wavefunctions within Kramers approach (arXiv:2602.18590)
   - Interface between the SOC code and NEVPT2/QDNEVPT2
   - Helper functions to plot spectra, calculate oscillator strengths, natural transition orbitals
   - Tests and examples for the SOC and g-tensor NEVPT2/QDNEVPT2 calculations

* Improvements:
   - More modular code and class structure with appropriate inheritance between the parent module class and method subclasses
   - Functions that are used by more than one method are now moved into tools or appropriate libraries (e.g., libsoc)

* Fixes:
   - Bug fix in QDNEVPT2 second-order RDM contributions
   - Updated reference values for the second-order RDM tests

